A Data Mapper Turbo Extract retrieves data from a single Salesforce object type, with support for fields from related objects. You can filter the data and select the fields to return.

Unlike a standard Data Mapper Extract, a Data Mapper Turbo Extract doesn't support formulas. The returned data type is Map<String, Object> and not SObject, you can't use it to update Product2 objects without reserializing. Thereâ€™s no Output tab, so you can't use mappings to structure the output. Custom JSON, default values, and translations aren't supported.

A Data Mapper Turbo Extract has two advantages over a standard Data Mapper Extract:

Simpler configuration

Better performance at runtime

To create a Data Mapper Turbo Extract, specify its name, input and output types, and permissions.

To configure a Data Mapper Turbo Extract, specify the object type, filters, fields to extract, and options.

Although a Data Mapper Turbo Extract retrieves from a single object type, you can select specific fields in related objects.

You can test the input and output of a Data Mapper Turbo Extract on the Preview tab.

A Data Mapper Turbo Extract retrieves Contacts for an Account having the specified Id.
title: Omnistudio Data Mapper Turbo Extract Overview
